text.section:
Notwithstanding any other provision of law, by publishing public notice, the Department may establish for a harvest reserve area:
The opening or closure of an area for the harvesting or conservation of oysters;
The harvest limit;
The seasons, days, and times when oysters may be harvested;
A minimum size limit of not less than 3 inches; and
A maximum size limit.

The Department shall use the following biological criteria for the opening and closing of a harvest reserve area:
Growth rates;
Disease prevalence and intensity;
Mortality thresholds; and
Biomass thresholds.
